<subSubSection id="C34C72A24B11FF9F14F9D25BFADBFB46" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14F9D25BFE2AFCAE" blockId="10.[136,1452,770,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F14F9D25BFF0AFCF2" box="[136,234,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
: Huguet del 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F1507D25BFDCFFCF2" author="Villar, E." box="[374,559,770,796]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref9729" refString="Huguet del Villar, E. (1947) Types de sol de l'Afrique du Nord. Fascicule 1 + 2. 288 pp." type="book" year="1947">Villar (1947: 79)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F16D4D25BFCB6FCF2" box="[677,854,770,796]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tazaotana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F16D4D25BFCB6FCF2" box="[677,854,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Abies tazaotana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
providing a description. No specimens or illustrations were cited in the protologue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14CCD212FE13FC43" blockId="10.[136,1452,770,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
In addition, we have not found any original material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F175ED212FC5CFC8A" box="[815,956,843,869]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tazaotana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F175ED212FC5CFC8A" box="[815,956,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A. tazaotana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the herbaria consulted (i.e., BM, K, MA, MAF, MPU, P, etc.). Accordingly, in the absence of any other extant original material, a 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B11FF9F100ED236FB38FC67" box="[1151,1240,879,905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">neotype</typeStatus>
can be designated according to Art. 9.8 of the 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F15CFD2CAFE0DFC43" box="[446,493,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">ICN</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14CCD2EEFADBFB46" blockId="10.[136,1452,770,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
In this sense, a modern specimen with available molecular data (AFLP and cpSSR), that was used and cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F14F9D283FEBFFC1A" author="Terrab, A. &amp; Talavera, S. &amp; Arista, M. &amp; Paun, O. &amp; Stuessy, T. F. &amp; Tremetsberger, K." box="[136,351,986,1012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="409 - 416" refId="ref11604" refString="Terrab, A., Talavera, S., Arista, M., Paun, O., Stuessy, T. F., Tremetsberger, K. (2007) Genetic diversity and geographic structure at chloroplast microsatellites (cpSSRs) in endangered West Mediterranean firs (Abies spp., Pinaceae). Taxon 56: 409 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 562012" type="journal article" year="2007">
Terrab 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F14A7D282FEEDFC1A" box="[214,269,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F151BD283FD4DFC1A" author="Sanchez-Robles, J. M. &amp; Balao, F. &amp; Terrab, A. &amp; Garcia-Castano, J. L. &amp; Ortiz, M. A. &amp; Vela, E. &amp; Talavera, S." box="[362,685,986,1012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="42 - 53" refId="ref11167" refString="Sanchez-Robles, J. M., Balao, F., Terrab, A., Garcia-Castano, J. L., Ortiz, M. A., Vela, E. &amp; Talavera, S. (2014) Phylogeography of SW Mediterranean firs: different European origins for the North African Abies species. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 79: 42 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2014.06.005" type="journal article" year="2014">
Sánchez-Robles 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F1652D282FDBAFC1A" box="[547,602,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F1694D283FC53FC1A" author="Balao, F. &amp; Lorenzo, M. T. &amp; Sanchez-Robles, J. M. &amp; Paun, O. &amp; Garcia-Castano, J. L. &amp; Terrab, A." box="[741,947,986,1012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="495 - 507" refId="ref7337" refString="Balao, F., Lorenzo, M. T., Sanchez-Robles, J. M., Paun, O., Garcia-Castano, J. L. &amp; Terrab, A. (2020) Early diversification and permeable species boundaries in the Mediterranean frs. Annals of Botany 125: 495 - 507. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aob / mcz 186" type="journal article" year="2020">
Balao 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F175DD282FC82FC1A" box="[812,866,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
is selected as the 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B11FF9F1005D282FB30FC1B" box="[1140,1232,987,1013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">neotype</typeStatus>
. This specimen was collected in Jbel Tazaot (NW 
<collectingCountry id="F34161B94B11FF9F15A6D2A6FDDEFBF7" box="[471,574,1023,1049]" name="Morocco" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Morocco</collectingCountry>
) and is preserved at 
<collectionCode id="ED47B9EC4B11FF9F1756D2A7FCBBFBF6" box="[807,859,1022,1048]" country="Spain" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14311" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14311" name="Universidad de Sevilla" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="Herbarium">SEV</collectionCode>
, with number 
<collectionCode id="ED47B9EC4B11FF9F178CD2A7FBD1FBF6" box="[1021,1073,1022,1048]" country="Spain" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14311" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14311" name="Universidad de Sevilla" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="Herbarium">SEV</collectionCode>
277703 (
<figureCitation id="136D3DAC4B11FF9F10ECD2A7FB02FBF7" box="[1181,1250,1022,1049]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[212,1368,195,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-22@11.[212,1374,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neotype of Abies tazaotana Côzar ex Huguet del Villar, SEV (number SEV 277703). Photography courtesy of Herbarium SEV; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605322/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). The provenance of the 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B11FF9F14A1D57AFEC9FBD3" box="[208,297,1059,1085]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">neotype</typeStatus>
matches the natural distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F16C6D57AFCA5FBD2" box="[695,837,1059,1085]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tazaotana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F16C6D57AFCA5FBD2" box="[695,837,1059,1085]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A. tazaotana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further, the specimen (a complete and well preserved branch with leaves and male cones) clearly represents the traditional concept (see e.g., Huguet del 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F10A3D51FFAB3FB8E" author="Villar, E." box="[1234,1363,1094,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref9729" refString="Huguet del Villar, E. (1947) Types de sol de l'Afrique du Nord. Fascicule 1 + 2. 288 pp." type="book" year="1947">Villar 1947</bibRefCitation>
, Franco 1950, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F14BFD533FE26FB6B" author="Maire, R. &amp; Weiller, M." box="[206,454,1130,1157]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref10212" refString="Maire, R. &amp; Weiller, M. (1952) Flore de l'Afrique du Nord, I. Paul Lechevalier, Paris." type="book" year="1952">Maire &amp; Weiller 1952</bibRefCitation>
) and the current application of the name (see e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F178DD533FAEBFB6A" author="Quezel, P. &amp; Barbero, M." box="[1020,1291,1130,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="145 - 178" refId="ref10871" refString="Quezel, P. &amp; Barbero, M. (1990) Les forets mediterraneennes. Problemes poses par leur signification historique, ecologique et leur conservation. Acta Botanica Malacitana 15: 145 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 15 i. 9300" type="journal article" year="1990">Quézel &amp; Barbero 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F1167D533FA46FB6A" author="Quezel, P." box="[1302,1446,1130,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="19 - 32" refId="ref10804" refString="Quezel, P. (1991) Structures de vegetation et flore en Afrique du Nord: leurs incidences sur les problemes de conservation. In: Rejdali, M. &amp; Heywood, V. H. (Eds.) Conservation des Ressources Vegetales. Actes Editions, Institut agronomique et veterinaire Hassan II, Rabat, Morocco, pp. 19 - 32." type="book chapter" year="1991">Quézel 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F14F9D5D7FE72FB46" author="Arista, M. &amp; Talavera, S." box="[136,402,1166,1192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="223 - 234" refId="ref7139" refString="Arista, M. &amp; Talavera, S. (1994) Phenology and anatomy of the reproductive phase of Abies pinsapo Boiss. (Pinaceae). Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 116: 223 - 234. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1994. tb 00431. x" type="journal article" year="1994">Arista &amp; Talavera 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F15ECD5D7FDA4FB47" author="Govaerts, R." box="[413,580,1166,1193]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref9607" refString="Govaerts, R. (1995) World Checklist of Seed Plants 1 (1, 2). MIM, Deurne. pp. 1 - 483 &amp; pp. 1 - 529." type="book chapter" year="1995">Govaerts 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F163ED5D7FC49FB46" author="Conifer Specialist Group" box="[591,937,1166,1192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref8267" refString="Conifer Specialist Group (1998) Abies pinsapo var. tazaotana. In: IUCN Red List of Threatened Species v. 2009.1. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org (accessed 9 May 2020)" type="url" year="1998">Conifer Specialist Group 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F17C5D5D7FB6DFB46" author="Esteban, L. G. &amp; De Palacios, P. &amp; Garcia Fernandez, F. &amp; Martin, J. A." box="[948,1165,1166,1192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="213 - 225" refId="ref8471" refString="Esteban, L. G., De Palacios, P., Garcia Fernandez, F. &amp; Martin, J. A. (2009) Wood anatomical relationships within Abies spp. from the Mediterranean area: a phyletic approach. Investigacion Agraria: Sistemas y Recursos Forestales 18: 213 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.5424 / fs / 2009182 - 01064" type="journal article" year="2009">
Esteban 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F1062D5D6FBACFB46" box="[1043,1100,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F10E9D5D7FACFFB46" author="Linares, J. C." box="[1176,1327,1166,1192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="619 - 630" refId="ref9977" refString="Linares, J. C. (2011) Biogeography and evolution of Abies (Pinaceae) in the Mediterranean Basin: the roles of long-term climatic change and glacial refugia. Journal of Biogeography 38: 619 - 630. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2699.2010.02458. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Linares 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
